</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1924" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1924" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Calhoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Calhoplophora</taxonomicName>
Berlese (1923) has the same type (
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1835" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">Hoplophora carinata C. L. Koch</taxonomicName>
) as 
<taxonomicName authority="Ewing, 1917" authorityName="Ewing" authorityYear="1917" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Tropacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tropacarus</taxonomicName>
Ewing (1917); for this reason it must be placed in the synonymy of the last-mentioned genus. Ewing did not know 
<taxonomicName authority="Ewing, 1917" authorityName="Ewing" authorityYear="1917" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Tropacarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">Tropacarus carinatus</taxonomicName>
, but founded his generic diagnosis on the descriptions of the species. Ewing and Berlese nientioned no other representatives of the genus; I added 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1835" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">Hoplophora pulcherrima Berlese</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipilus" subGenus="Trachyhoplophora">Phthiracarus (Trachyhoplophora) brevipilus Berlese</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
